        "rich_text_9hwRAc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Heading",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>The Meaning Of Toi Et Moi Rings: Two Stones, One Story </h1>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "follow_us_ygY8aG": {
          "type": "follow_us",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Follow Us on"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ccxpK9": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>In the search for rings that feel personal, meaningful, and deeply symbolic of the love of soulmates, only few match the beauty of a ‘toi et moi’ ring. Pronounced as ‘twah ay mwah’, ‘toi et moi’ is a French phrase that literally translates to ‘you and me.’ In the world of fine jewelry, toi et moi rings are one of the few designs that feel intimate and poetic. Usually, gemstone rings are chosen with just solitaire rings in mind, but the world of fine jewelry offers you with unique options such as the toi et moi <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-ring\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"engagement ring\">engagement ring</a>. Let’s first understand the meaning of toi et moi rings and then deep dive into how you can choose the right toi et moi ring for yourself easily without any confusion!</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_kKqW7n": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Meaning of Toi Et Moi Rings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Meaning of Toi Et Moi Rings</h2>",
            "custom_id": "the"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_yYFrht": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Meaning of Toi Et Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The ‘Toi et Moi’ ring meaning is representative of the dualities - contrasting personalities that complement each other and become whole. Each stone in this two stones ring reflects an aspect of you and your partner. Modern couples are choosing toi et moi rings because they see beyond sparkle - they see symbolism and understated luxury. This meaningful choice reflects that opposites attract or signify the similarities that bonds a couple together. Some couples even choose rings that reflect their personalities - a bold emerald paired with a soft pear diamond. Many choose stones that reflect their stories, birth months or shared milestones. After all, these two stones come together to become one story. </p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_BxFmqg": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "A Brief History of Toi et Moi Rings",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>A Brief History of Toi et Moi Rings</h3>",
            "custom_id": "a"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_wrPRca": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "A Brief History of Toi Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Before diving into what makes a toi et moi engagement ring unique and how should you choose one, lets know the history of toi et moi rings. These rings may be trending today, but they are timeless pieces with origins steeped in centuries of romance. The most iconic and prime example dates back to 1796 when Napoleon Bonaparte proposed to Joséphine with a toi et moi ring. Back then, this devotion of love and expression took almost a rebellious form of romance for its time. Then came the Victorian Era when the popularity of these double stone rings took precedence over a single stone ring as symbolism got woven in every piece of fine jewelry crafted in that time. The trend has re-emerged in 21st century with people wanting jewelry that feels more personal, bespoke and intentionally chosen - in which diamonds are crafted to tell stories of love.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Jbd43L": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What Makes Toi Et Moi Rings Unique As Engagement Rings?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What Makes Toi Et Moi Rings Unique As Engagement Rings?</h2>",
            "custom_id": "what"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_zpxzBh": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>‘You and Me’ - The ‘<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/toi-et-moi-engagement-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Toi et Moi Engagement RIngs\">Toi et Moi</a>’ ring celebrates two distinct stones side by side, symbolising the union of two souls. The marquise stone adds vintage drama, while the emerald cut adds refined sophistication. Together they represent the essence of modern love. If your love story is the story of opposites attract, if you are the yin to their yang, and complement each other, this design is for you. </p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_PYNpgj": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Marquise & Emerald Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Say yes if you appreciate artistry and symbolism. This custom diamond engagement ring is for those who value meaning as much as beauty</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ejh96n": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Elegance Trilogy Diamond Ring ",
          "settings": {
